hopobject.body: I live in London walkingforhealth.org.uk/walkfinder The scientists looked specifically at chromium-53 and chromium-52 isotopes. Chromium-53 is the heavier isotope, and demonstrates greater solubility than chromium-52 when oxidized. Consequently, soils that have been exposed to molecular oxygen will possess little chromium-53, as this isotope’s solubility resulted in it being washed away by rain water. Meanwhile, chromium-53 will be present in much greater concentrations in sea sediment, following the afore-mentioned weathering process.
